LISTERIOSIS - FRANCE (02)
*************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
See Also
Listeriosis - France 20000219195424
Listeriosis - France: background 20000220192206
[1
Date: Sun, 20 Feb 2000 21:30:53 +0200
From: Arnon Shimshony <isr-agri@dircon.co.uk>
Source: Times of London, 20 Feb 2000 [edited

Two newborn babies are among seven people who have died in an outbreak of
listeri[osis in France believed to have been caused by processed meat. The
sell-by
date of these meats has been reduced from 42 to 30 days.
--
Arnon Shimshony
e-mail: isr-agri@dircon.co.uk
*****
[2
Date: Mon, 21 Feb 2000 07:15:04 -0500
From: Abramo Ottolenghi <ottolenghi.1@osu.edu>
Source: News media, on-line editions, 21 Feb 2000
According to the on-line editions of Le Monde and Nicematin the outbreak is
due to a single strain and has been seen in 19 Departments (not named)
throughout France. The source has not been identified. There have been 30
cases with 7 deaths since November.
--
